ractional calculus and anomalous diffusion are closely connected with heavy tail limit theorems. Heavy tails are applied in finance, insurance, physics, geophysics, cell biology, ecology, medicine, and computer engineering. The goal of this book is to prepare graduate students in probability for research in the area of fractional calculus, anomalous diffusion, and heavy tails. Many interesting problems in this area remain open. This book will guide the motivated reader to understand the essential background needed to read and unerstand current research papers, and to gain the insights and techniques needed to begin making their own contributions to this rapidly growing field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aAnomale Diffusion. 4aGebrochene Analysis. 4aGrenzwertsatz. 7aMATHEMATICS / Probability & Statistics / Stochastic Processes.2bisacsh1 aSikorskii, Alla, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2019 Englishz978311061040608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2019z9783110606362oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831105591490 cprintz978311055907140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311056024440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110560244423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110560244.jpg  a978-3-11-061040-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_MTP